task.summary: Added some safe guards to the HeatableItemRegistry.
Added Backwards compat for older JEI versions.
Fixing some of the TextureControllers not having the VertexColor Override.
Added custom coloring for ToolTips using the new MultiColoredFontRenderer in SC.
Retrieving Git username and Password for Travis.
Removed Username and Password printouts after change and retrieval.
Added Uploading to the Maven Repo Again.

Fixed Recipes with an Null-Item in the resultstack being attempted to remove from the game.
Closes #30

Hopefully fixing a problem when creating heated items. The Temperature bar should be baked with DefaultVertexFormat.Item, instead it was baked with what the actual original Item was requiring. This was causing issues with some items.
Hopefully fixes https://github.com/SmithsGaming/SmithsCore/issues/8
Updated to the new SmithsCore version.
Improved models on Forge and Fixes and Such.
Added a catch to a fluid that does not seem to have a material. It is outputted on the log and then removed.
Also fixing the HeatableItemRegistery to a point: Fluids were amount sensitive, causing fluids with an unknown amount to crash the game if the material would be retrieved.
